From: Ilya Leoshkevich <iii@linux.ibm.com>
Date: Thu, 21 Aug 2025 13:25:56 +0200
Subject: selftests/bpf: Add a missing newline to the "bad arch spec" message
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc1
Git-commit: b68dfcc12a320b85cd33d0d673ea620da08d0aec
References: jsc#PED-14653

Fix error messages like this one:

  parse_test_spec:FAIL:569 bad arch spec: 's390x'process_subtest:FAIL:1153 Can't parse test spec for program 'may_goto_simple'

Signed-off-by: Ilya Leoshkevich <iii@linux.ibm.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250821113339.292434-3-iii@linux.ibm.com
Signed-off-by: Alexei Starovoitov <ast@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_loader.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_loader.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/test_loader.c
@@ -566,7 +566,7 @@ static int parse_test_spec(struct test_l
 			} else if (strcmp(val, "RISCV64") == 0) {
 				arch = ARCH_RISCV64;
 			} else {
-				PRINT_FAIL("bad arch spec: '%s'", val);
+				PRINT_FAIL("bad arch spec: '%s'\n", val);
 				err = -EINVAL;
 				goto cleanup;
 			}
